abstract:
We propose a new kind of capacitorless DRAM: 1Transistor Quantum Well structure, which has a ldquostorage pocketrdquo for holes within the body. This memory gives the opportunity to engineer spatial hole distribution within the body of the device, which is not possible with the conventional 1T-DRAMs. Using this novel device, we demonstrate approximately two order-of-magnitude increase in the drain-current (
<i xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Id</i>
) difference between the reads of two states of the memory.

Multiantenna wireless systems have been well studied in achieving high data rates. In this paper, we improve a subspace-based blind channel estimation technique for multi- input multi-output (MIMO) orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) approach based on tracking the subspace recursively. The recursive subspace algorithm has a computational complexity of O(J
<sup xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">2</sup>
) , where the J is the input vector dimension. The simulation results show that the improved estimator's capability is similar to the source approach, but deeply decrease the computational complexity.
